{
  "text": "Detail description of this approach is discussed. Equation (14) presents the primary optimization function for service offloading. Equation [CITATION_1] describes that the actual service latency, D t to , is to be greater than the threshold service latency, D th . The bandwidth requirement of edge device, B req i , is to be greater than the threshold bandwidth requirement, B th , as shown in [CITATION_2] . Equation [CITATION_3] represents that the service offloading rate of edge device, H i (Y, t), is to be grater than the threshold offloading rate, H th . The QoS-level, Q i , is to be greater than the threshold QoS-level, Q th , as shown in [CITATION_4] . Equation [CITATION_5] denotes that the total estimated price for edge device, P tot i , is to be grater than the threshold price, P th . Solving the optimization problem using Lagrangian multipliers, we get",
